  "prompt": "How do you cook pork chops in the oven?",
  "response": "Cooking pork chops in the oven is a straightforward process, and here\u2019s a simple recipe to achieve juicy and flavorful results.\n\n### Ingredients:\n- 4 bone-in or boneless pork chops (about 1 inch thick)\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil or melted butter\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- Optional: garlic powder, onion powder, paprika, rosemary, thyme, or any preferred seasonings\n\n### Instructions:\n\n1. **Preheat the Oven:**\n   Preheat your oven to 375\u00b0F (190\u00b0C).\n\n2. **Prepare the Pork Chops:**\n   - Pat the pork chops dry with paper towels. This helps to get a nice sear and prevents steaming.\n   - Rub both sides with olive oil or melted butter.\n   - Season generously with salt, pepper, and any additional spices you prefer.\n\n3. **Sear (Optional but Recommended):**\n   - In an oven-safe skillet (cast iron works well), heat a tablespoon of olive oil over medium-high heat.\n   - Once hot, add the pork chops and sear for about 3-4 minutes on each side, until they are golden brown. This step adds flavor but can be skipped if you're looking for a quicker method.\n\n4. **Bake:**\n   - If you seared the chops, transfer the skillet to the preheated oven. If you didn\u2019t sear them, place the seasoned pork chops on a baking sheet or in a baking dish.\n   - Bake for about 20-30 minutes, or until the internal temperature reaches 145\u00b0F (63\u00b0C). The exact cooking time will depend on the thickness of the chops.\n\n5. **Rest:**\n   - Once cooked, remove the pork chops from the oven and let them rest for about 5 minutes. This helps the juices redistribute throughout the meat, making it juicier.\n\n6. **Serve:**\n   - Serve the pork chops with your favorite sides such as mashed potatoes, vegetables, or a fresh salad.\n\n### Tips:\n- For added flavor, you can marinate the pork chops for a few hours or overnight in a mixture of olive oil, vinegar, herbs, and spices.\n- Additionally, you can add a layer of topping like breadcrumbs or cheese for extra crunch and flavor during the baking step.\n\nEnjoy your delicious oven-baked pork chops!",
